07479nam a22010215i 9783035623666DE-B159720221201113901.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221201t20212022sz     fo  d z      eng d  a97830356236667 a10.1515/97830356236662doi  a(DE-B1597)574096  a(OCoLC)1257323842  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH 7aDES0000002bisacsh00aNERD - New Experimental Research in Design 2 :bPositions and Perspectives /ced. by Ralf Michel, Wolfgang Jonas, Michelle Christensen. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2021] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (160 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aBoard of International Research in Design00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tPreface -- tDesign as Critical Inquiry: Politics, Performativity and Practice -- t‘Flatten the Curve’. The Performative Embodiment of Image, Speech, and Gestures in Scientific Communication from a Design Research Perspective -- tDesigning in Troubling Times: Experimental Engagements with Socio-Ecological Challenges at the Uroboros Festival -- tImagining Offjects in the Fractiverse -- tMaking A Cup: An Autoethnographic Study on the Domain of Making and its Distinction from Designing -- tParticipatory Animation with Young People: an Interdisciplinary Approach to Engagement -- tResearch through Design and Reflection on Poetic Curiosity -- tDesign by Act: A New Look at Design Activism and its Actors -- tDesigning a Computational Interface for the Study of Collections: ‘Grouper’ as a Research Tool -- tMake/believe or Make-believe? – Exploring Collective Futures through Crafting Environments in Response to an Immersive Narrative -- tPost Social: Towards Design Beyond the Human -- tAnthroponix: Upcycling Urine as Collective Design Practice -- tAuthors and Editors0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDesign is inextricably interwoven with all aspects of life and has even produced its own astonishing genre of research. Design research opens up new perspectives of interdisciplinary empiricism, joining with economics, sociology, technology, and philosophy to produce analyses and syntheses that get to the heart of daily life. The twelve contributions from international authors that comprise this book vividly make this case. They cover the relationship between subject and object, animation, all forms of representation, design activism, and many other themes. This book is intended to inspire discussion. Its target reader is anyone seeking to expand their understanding of design, to fundamentally improve their praxis, and to more deeply appreciate life in all of its aspects.  aDesign mischt sich unvermeidlich in alle Aspekte des Lebens ein und hat dabei eine erstaunliche eigene Qualität von Forschung entwickelt: Design-Forschung schafft neue Perspektiven interdisziplinärer Empirie, verbindet sich in Analysen und Synthesen mit Ökonomie, Soziologie, Technologie, Ökologie und Philosophie und bewegt sich so inmitten des alltäglichen Lebens. Anschaulich macht das Buch dies mit 12 Beiträgen von internationalen Autorinnen und Autoren: zur Frage des Verhältnisses von Subjekt und Objekt, zu Animation, zu jeglicher Form von Darstellung, zu Design-Aktivismus und anderen Themen. Eine Grundlage für anregende Diskussionen, ein Buch für alle, die neue Einsichten suchen, jegliche Praxis grundlegend verbessern und das Leben in all seinen Aspekten verstehen wollen.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aDesign. 4aForschung. 4aGesellschaft. 7aDESIGN / General.2bisacsh1 aChristensen, Michelle, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aConradi, Florian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDobler, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/